    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "I'm using IPython 6.2.1 and I had the same issue as @karlacio.\r\n\r\nUsing the example from here: https://github.com/ipython/ipython/blob/master/examples/IPython%20Kernel/gui/gui-wx.py\r\n\r\nand, applying the fix that @karlacio recommended (this is line 118 in `inputhook_wx3` in IPython 6.2.1) - i.e.:\r\n\r\n**`assert wx.Thread_IsMain()`** -> **`assert wx.IsMainThread()`**\r\n\r\none obtains a new error: \r\n\r\n> AttributeError: module 'wx' has no attribute 'Timer'\r\n\r\nwhich appears to be solved by updating \r\n\r\n**`app.ProcessIdle()`** to **`evtloop.ProcessIdle()`** \r\n\r\non **`<Python version>/site-packages/IPython/lib/inputhookwx.py`** and in **`<Python version>/site-packages/IPython/terminal/pt_inputhooks/wx.py`**\r\n\r\nHaving referenced this updated sample from wxPython: https://github.com/wxWidgets/wxPython/blob/4b20d984aaaf4a5d7dfcdc1490c0b42489d452f7/samples/mainloop/mainloop.py\r\n\r\nApplying these fixes solves the issue, and one is able to run the example cited without any further problems."
  },
